COMMENT ON TABLE activity_submission IS 'Submission of data and information related to a groundwater wells.';
COMMENT ON TABLE activity_submission_water_quality IS 'Water quality characteristic of the well.';
COMMENT ON TABLE aquifer IS 'A geological formation, a group of geological formations, or a part of one or more geological formations that is groundwater bearing and capable of storing, transmitting and yielding groundwater.';
COMMENT ON TABLE aquifer_demand_code IS 'Describes the level of groundwater use at the time aquifer was mapped; i.e., High, Moderate, Low.';
COMMENT ON TABLE aquifer_material_code IS 'Describes the broad grouping of geological material found in the aquifer, i.e., Sand and Gravel, Sand, Gravel, Bedrock';
COMMENT ON TABLE aquifer_productivity_code IS 'Describes the aquifer''s productivity which represent an aquifers ability to transmit and yield groundwater; i.e., Low, Moderate, High';
COMMENT ON TABLE aquifer_subtype_code IS 'Categorizes an aquifer based on how it was formed geologically (depositional description). Understanding of how aquifers were formed governs important attributes such as their productivity, vulnerability to contamination as well as proximity and likelihood of hydraulic connection to streams.  The code value is a combination of an aquifer type represented by a number and an optional letter representing a more specific aquifer sub-type. E.g. aquifer sub-type code 6b is comprised of the aquifer type number (6: Crystalline bedrock aquifers) and subtype letter (b) specifically described as: Fractured crystalline (igneous intrusive or metamorphic, meta-sedimentary, meta-volcanic, volcanic) rock aquifers.  Code values range from 1a to 6b.';
COMMENT ON TABLE aquifer_vulnerability_code IS 'Describes an aquiferâ€™s relative intrinsic vulnerability to impacts from human activities on the land surface.  Vulnerability is based on: the type, thickness, and extent of geologic materials above the aquifer, depth to water table (or to top of confined aquifer), and type of aquifer materials, i.e., Low, Moderate, High.';
COMMENT ON TABLE aquifer_well IS 'Cross reference table that connects the well to the aquifer.  It resolves the many to many relationship between wells and aquifers.  One well can be in 1-many aquifers, and one aquifer can have 1-many wells in it.';
COMMENT ON TABLE bcgs_number IS 'Placeholder table comment.';
COMMENT ON TABLE bedrock_material_code IS 'Bedrock material encountered during drilling and reported in lithologic description.';
COMMENT ON TABLE bedrock_material_descriptor_code IS 'An adjective that describes the characteristics of the bedrock material in more detail.';
COMMENT ON TABLE casing IS 'Piping or tubing installed in a well to support the sides of the well.  The casing is comprised of a production (inner tube) and surface (outer tube) and can be made of a variety of materials.';
COMMENT ON TABLE casing_code IS 'Describes the casing component (piping or tubing installed in a well) as either production (inner tube), surface (outer tube), or open hole.';
COMMENT ON TABLE casing_material_code IS 'Describes the material that the casing is made of.';
COMMENT ON TABLE decommission_method_code IS 'Describes the method used to fill the well to close it permanently.';
COMMENT ON TABLE development_method_code IS 'The methods used to remove the fine sediment and other organic or inorganic material that immediately surrounds the well screen, the drill hole or the intake area at the bottom of the well.  E.g. Air Lifting, Bailing, Jetting, Pumping, Surging.  ''Other'' can also be specified.';
COMMENT ON TABLE drilling_company IS 'Company or organization that was associated with the individual that conducted the work on the well.';
COMMENT ON TABLE drilling_method_code IS 'Represents the method that was used  to drill or construct a well.  E.g. Excavated, Dual Rotary, Driving, Other, Unknown.';
COMMENT ON TABLE filter_pack_material_code IS 'Materials used in the filter pack, which are placed in the annulus of the well between the borehole wall and the well screen, and are used to settle-out fine grained particles that may otherwise enter the well.  I.e. Fine gravel, very course sand, very fine gravel, other.';
COMMENT ON TABLE filter_pack_material_size_code IS 'Codes for the sizes of the material used to pack a well filter. Some examples of filter pack sizes are: 1.0 - 2.0 mm, 2.0 - 4.0 mm, 4.0 - 8.0 mm.';
COMMENT ON TABLE ground_elevation_method_code IS 'Method used to determine the ground elevation of a well. E.g.  GPS, Altimeter, Differential GPS, Level, 1:50,000 map, 1:20,000 map.';
COMMENT ON TABLE gwells_survey IS 'A stand-alone table used by the minstry to record client satisfaction surveys.  Temporary table to be removed.';
COMMENT ON TABLE hydraulic_property IS 'Placeholder table comment.';
COMMENT ON TABLE intended_water_use_code IS 'The intended use of the water in a water supply well as reported by the driller at time of work completion on the well. E.g Private domestic, irrigation, water supply system, Industrial commercial, and unknown.';
COMMENT ON TABLE land_district_code IS 'Legal Land District used to help identify the property where the well is located.  E.g. Alberni, Barclay, Cariboo.';
COMMENT ON TABLE licenced_status_code IS 'Options as to whether or not a well has been granted a water licesne under the Water Sustainability Act.  This information comes from eLicensing. i.e. Unlicensed, Licensed, Historical';
COMMENT ON TABLE liner_material_code IS 'Describes the material of the piping or tubing installed in a well which protects the well pump or other works in the well from damage.  i.e. PVC, Other';
COMMENT ON TABLE liner_perforation IS 'Describes the depths at which the liner is perforated in a well to help improve water flow at the bottom of the well.  Some wells are perforated instead of having a screen installed.';
COMMENT ON TABLE lithology_colour_code IS 'Describes the colour of the lithologic material identified at time of drilling.  E.g. Black, dark, tan, rust-coloured';
COMMENT ON TABLE lithology_description IS 'Describes the different lithologic qualities, characteristics, and materials found at different depths while drilling.';
COMMENT ON TABLE lithology_description_code IS 'Standard terms used to characterize the different qualities of lithologic materials. E.g. dry, loose, weathered, soft.';
COMMENT ON TABLE lithology_hardness_code IS 'Code that represents the hardness of the material that a well is drilled into (the lithology).   E.g. Very hard, Hard, Dense, Stiff, Medium, Loose, Soft, Very soft.';
COMMENT ON TABLE lithology_material_code IS 'Code that describes the material noted for lithology. E.g. Rock, Clay, Sand, Unspecified,';
COMMENT ON TABLE lithology_moisture_code IS 'Code that describes the level of water within the lithologic layer.  i.e. Dry, Damp, Moist, Wet';
COMMENT ON TABLE lithology_structure_code IS 'ASK DEVELOPERS TO DELETE THIS TABLE';
COMMENT ON TABLE ltsa_owner IS 'ASK DEVELOPERS WHAT THIS TABLE IS BEING USED FOR, call it well_owner?  Owner exists in well table, why do we need this?';
COMMENT ON TABLE obs_well_status_code IS 'Status of an observation well within the Provincial Groundwater Observation Well Network.  I.e. Active is a well that is currently being used to collect groundwater information, and inactive is a well that is no longer being used to collect groundwater information.';
COMMENT ON TABLE online_survey IS 'Delete this table';
COMMENT ON TABLE perforation IS 'ASK DEVELOPERS IF THIS TABLE IS BEING USED.  Analagous to liner_performation table.';
COMMENT ON TABLE profile IS 'ASK DEVELOPERS to describe this table';
COMMENT ON TABLE province_state_code IS 'Province or state used for the mailing address for the company';
COMMENT ON TABLE quality_concern_code IS 'Extent of documented concerns of contaminants in the aquifer at the time of mapping. i.e. isloated, local, regional, none.';
COMMENT ON TABLE registries_accredited_certificate_code IS 'Describes the valid qualifications or certificates (prescribed qualifications) as issued by the certifying authority; used to register a well driller or well pump installer.  Individuals registered prior to 2006 may have qualified under the grandparenting provision. E.g., Water Well Driller Certificate issued by BC to register an applicant as a Well Driller.';
COMMENT ON TABLE registries_activity_code IS 'Describes the registered individual''s allowable activity on a well; i.e. Well Driller, or Pump Installer.';
COMMENT ON TABLE registries_application IS 'Placeholder table comment.';
COMMENT ON TABLE registries_application_status_code IS 'Describes the statuses that the application for well driller or well pump installer registration goes through, i.e., Pending, Incomplete, Not Approved, Registered';
