COMMENT ON TABLE screen IS 'Describes the screen type, diameter of screen, and the depth at which the screen is installed in a well.';
COMMENT ON TABLE screen_assembly_type_code IS 'Describes the different components of a screen.  A single well screen could be composed of several assembly layers, each layer may have a different screen assembly type.  Some examples include: K-packer, Riser Pipe, Screen, Screen blank, Tail Pipe.';
COMMENT ON TABLE screen_bottom_code IS 'Valid categories used to identify the type of bottom on a well screen.  It provides for a standard commonly understood code and description for screen bottoms.  Some examples include: Bail, Plate, Plug. ''Other'' can also be specified.';
COMMENT ON TABLE screen_intake_method_code IS 'Valid categories used to identify the type of intake mechanism for a well screen.  It provides for a standard commonly understood code and description for screen intake codes.  Some examples include: Open bottom, Screen, Uncased hole.';
COMMENT ON TABLE screen_material_code IS 'Describes the different materials that makes up the screen on a well. E.g. Plastic, Stainless Steel, Other.';
COMMENT ON TABLE screen_opening_code IS 'Valid categories used to identify the type of opening on a well screen.  It provides for a standard commonly understood code and description for screen openings. E.g. Continuous Slot, Perforated Pipe, Slotted.';
COMMENT ON TABLE screen_type_code IS 'Valid categories for the type of well screen installed in a well.  i.e. Pipe size, Telescope, Other';
COMMENT ON TABLE surface_seal_material_code IS 'Valid materials used for creating the surface seal for a well.   A surface seal is a plug that prevents surface runoff from getting into the aquifer or well and contaminating the water.  E.g. Bentonite clay, Concrete grout, Sand cement grout, Other.';
COMMENT ON TABLE surface_seal_method_code IS 'Valid methods used to create the surface seal for a well.  i.e. Poured, Pumped, Other.';
COMMENT ON TABLE surficial_material_code IS 'ASK DEVELOPERS TO DELETE THIS TABLE, we don''t belive it is being used or necessary.';
COMMENT ON TABLE water_quality_characteristic IS 'Valid values that can be used to indicate the quality of the water for a well as recorded at time of work.  E.g. Clear, Cloudy, Fresh, Gas, Salty, Sediment.';
COMMENT ON TABLE water_quality_colour_code IS 'Valid values of the colour of the water as recorded at time of work.  E.g. Orange, Black, Clear, Other';
COMMENT ON TABLE water_use_code IS 'Describes the type of known water use of an aquifer at the time of mapping.  It indicates the variability or diversity of uses of the aquifer water as a supply source.  I.e. Domestic, Multiple, Potential Domestic';
COMMENT ON TABLE well IS 'Describes how a well was constructed, altered, decomissioned over time.  Includes information related to who owns the well, location of well, the lithologic description as well as other information related to the construction of the well.';
COMMENT ON TABLE well_activity_code IS 'Placeholder table comment.';
COMMENT ON TABLE well_class_code IS 'Valid classifications as defined in the Groundwater Protection Regulation of the Water Act.  E.g. Water Supply, Monitoring, Recharge / Injection, Dewatering / Drainage, Remediation, Geotechnical.';
COMMENT ON TABLE well_status_code IS 'Represents the status of a well as defined in the Groundwater Protection Regulation of the Water Act. i.e. New, Abandoned (exists in Wells but will not be used for E-Wells), Alteration, Closure, Other.';
COMMENT ON TABLE well_subclass_code IS 'Valid methods used to further classify a well within the main classification (well_class_code).   It provides for a standard commonly understood code and description for well sub-classifcation as defined in the Groundwater Protection Regulation of the Water Act . i.e. Domestic, Borehole, Closed Loop Geothermal, Non-domestic,Permanent, Special, Temporary, Test Pit.';
COMMENT ON TABLE well_water_quality IS 'A cross reference table maintaining the list wells and their water quality characteristics.  One well can have many water quatlity characteristics, e.g Clear, Cloudy, Salty.';
COMMENT ON TABLE well_yield_unit_code IS 'Describes the unit of measure that was used for the well yield.   All codes except the U.S. Gallons per Minute has been retired as all data from April 2019 will be reported in U.S. Gallons per Minute.  E.g of other codes that have been used in the past are Gallons per Minute (U.S./Imperial), Dry Hole, Unknown Yield.';
COMMENT ON TABLE wells_decommissiondescription IS 'A cross refernce table maintaining the list of wells that have been decomissioned and the materials used to fill the well when decomissioned.   E.g. Bentonite chips, Native sand or gravel, Commercial gravel/pea gravel.';
COMMENT ON TABLE wells_decommissionmaterialcode IS 'Describes the material used to fill a well when decomissioned.  E.g. Bentonite chips, Native sand or gravel, Commercial gravel/pea gravel.';
COMMENT ON TABLE xform_aquifers IS 'ASK DEVELOPERS TO DELETE THIS TABLE';
COMMENT ON TABLE yield_estimation_method_code IS 'Describes the valid methods that can be used to estimate the yield of a well.  E.g. Air Lifting, Bailing, Pumping, Other.';


